NEXT3(TM) is a flavor of the widely used Ext3 file system with built-in support for snapshots. 
Developed by CTERA Networks, NEXT3 is licensed under the GPL.

This package contains a standalone ext4dev module with NEXT3 snaphsots support.
It is available for download on the NEXT3 project download page [http://next3.sourceforge.net/files/].

The package consists of the following files:
README - This file.
Makefile - Download, build, install and test ext4dev kernel module and utils.
docs/COPYING - GPL License.
docs/CHANGELOG - Release notes.
docs/INSTALL - Build and install instructions.
docs/HOWTO - Getting started with snapshots.
docs/BUGS - Open issues.
bin/snapshot.ext4dev - snapshots management script.
bin/{fsck,mkfs,tunefs,lsattr/chattr}.ext4dev - Pre-compiled (for x86_64) e2fsprogs utils with snapshot support patches.

For more information, please visit the NEXT3 wiki [http://sourceforge.net/apps/mediawiki/next3].
Please post support questions to the next3-users mailing list [https://lists.sourceforge.net/lists/listinfo/next3-users].
Please post bugs and technical questions to the next3-devel mailing list [https://lists.sourceforge.net/lists/listinfo/next3-devel].
For other requests please contact Amir Goldstein <amir73il@users.sourceforge.net>.

